\subsection{Galois splitting model of a local field}
\begin{definition}\label{lf.galois_splitting_model}
\uses{lf.galois_closure_invariants}
Let $K$ be a finite extension of $\Q_p$.
A **Galois splitting model** of $K$ is an irreducible polynomial $f\in\Q[x]$ such that $K\cong \Q_p[x]/(f)$, and the Galois group of $f$ over $\Q$ is isomorphic to the Galois group of $f$ over $\Q_p$. 

Most, but not all, local number fields have Galois splitting models.

With a Galois splitting model, the computation of various invariants related to $K$, such as the {{KNOWL('lf.galois_closure_invariants', 'Galois invariants')}}, can be carried out more easily using $f$.
\end{definition}


